column5: Ok the season will soon be hear the hunters must be getting ichey ok *Boys & Gals * aaa
Im off Friday and will be out in the AM. Good luck fishfarmer and play safe out there.
Leaving soon.. for 10 days of glorious unfetteredness.
Hey Boss. Do you have anterless or buck only? Man this is getting...... Best of luck.stay safe.

Was out fishing yesterday and found my self wading through the river...came up to a farmers field and saw 6 deer out there feeding on the grass...was beautiful to see, wish I had my camera....  Good luck out there killers!

did they look something like this ???? my buddy shot this today at the Bruce Nuke Plant....but it was gone by the time the armed security got there to shoot this terrorist...glad he got a pic of it though ...

Here in NYS gun season in the southern tire doesn't start until Nov 21st........but duck season starts Oct 24th and pheasant starts Oct 17th....  Last Saturday we all met up at deer camp and cut some of the fields plus trimmed around our tree stands.  I decided this year I am getting a bit old to climb into my tree stand and so I built a ladder out of 2 - 2X4X12'. Now it's a bit heavy.....so I will be struggling to get it there (any volunteers to help..:<)  The best thing about opening day in deer camp is we get to see all those who we haven't seen since last year.....my son and nephew come in from out of town and it don't get no better than that.  Over the last two years we did lose two older comrades and they will be dearly missed.  Bob
TY Be sure to post our kills in the coming days. Hope you enjoy.
[quote name= Good luck out there killers!   You mean "HARVESTERS"
Bob, thats the whole thing about this sport. Friends,some drinks, and hopfully some meat to share.
Thank you.Nice Davey Crockett hat BTW.LOL  Im waiting for the land owner to take down the corn here, before I start blasting the birds.Right now,Im waiting for a nice brown fur friend to walk by.
Iam 90% packed iam leaving tommorow right after work from oct 2nd to 13th heading up north of sudbury from guelph
best of luck my hunting brothers.Just made some venison stew some of the last bit left from last year. Joe
U can't hunt   Good luck out there...u will need it

Went out today saw a doe but not the area i have a doe tag for.  Out from 7:00am-6:30pm  When i got back to my truck someone tried to break into the tuck buck but since my tannou cover locks when my tail gate is they only open one side and gae up as they still couldnt get their hands in.   Pisses me off peopl try this.
I miss venison stew Joe. Been a couple years now.  It,s all about to change.  TY   I,ll be sure to have pic,s of the gutting,just for you.   Buster, GL bud.

Just got back in from the woods. Our bow season in Indiana just started today. I saw three button bucks and one small eight pointer. Not sure what you guys are allowed in Ontario but in Indiana we can only harvest one buck. However in my county you can take about 11 does between bow, shotgun and muzzleloader. Can't wait to get back out there this weekend.
Good luck aim true

we started this past weekend, however due too my wifes pending  divorce resolution, i decided it would be better(cheaper) to go to the mother in laws birthday party instead of going hunting, i havent had a chance since then, been trying to get a little farm work done, but hope to get out this weekend
seen a doe and a fawn tonight . Had the doe at about 30 yards but im waiting on big poppa !
what you never killed something??   man your post make me laugh!!!!  yours specifically!!   and like others have stated, it's called selective harvesting!!!

Better harvesting than getting killed on the HWY and going to the dump. Plus saves our lives and crashes on our HWY's What about fish catch and keep, very tasty, same with Deer. Good luck out their boy's and gal's, BE SAFE The other Fish Farmer

Remember that young,n I got a pic of at the field stand,well she made a visit this morning 7:32 to be percise.Just as close as the pic.I had to pass aswell. Cant believe I passed up.Only day two of many.Lots of time. At 9am headed to the climber for a couple hours.Nada.  Lets hope the rain holds for abit saturday am.  Good luck to you aswell,the other Fishfarmer.

I have deer questions, but didn't want to start a new NF post to ask it.  I figured i'd add it here.  Here's my Q: Do deer eat soya beans before the beens have been cut?  Or do they wait to munch on that stuff untill after it's be cut down??  I have three properties that I hunt in Simcoe for deer, and they all have Soya beans in them.  2 of the properties have a fraction of the sign they had last year when corn was planted.  I'm wondering if the deer sign will pick up after the Soya bean harvest??  Sunday will be my first day in the stand.  AM and PM -- A marathon of sorts.  Thanks gents.

Yes they do.The land owner where I hunt, has seen them grazing out there.Problem is,theres no place for a stand there.Well I could put a tripod stand,I already got to many ares to cover already.LOL  GL.
